snippet: Preliminary returns from parliamentary elections showed voters on track to oust the conservative government, an apparent reflection of public anger over austerity measures imposed in response to the European financial crisis.
abstract: Preliminary returns from Lithuania's parliamentary elections show voters on track to oust  Prime Min Andrius Kubilius's conservative government, apparent reflection of public anger over tax increases and other austerity measures imposed in response to  European financial crisis.
lead_paragraph: Preliminary returns from parliamentary elections showed voters on track to oust the conservative government, an apparent reflection of public anger over austerity measures imposed in response to the European financial crisis.

headline.seo: Preliminary Returns in Lithuania: Prime Minister’s Party Is Losing
headline.main: A Shift to the Left in Lithuania Jeopardizes the Ruling Party
headline.print_headline: A Shift to the Left in Lithuania Jeopardizes the Ruling Party
